# ── WebRTC ICE Servers ────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# JSON array of RTCIceServer objects.
# Invalid/empty → fallback to two public STUN servers (Google + Twilio).
#
# Credentials must match TURN_USER/TURN_PASS in docker-compose.yml.
# Dev defaults: username=signchat, credential=signchat
# (change for production — see scripts/cloud-deploy.md)
#
# See docs/webrtc-connectivity.md for full guides.
# Env is baked at Next.js compile time — restart dev server after changes.
#
# ─── STUN only (same machine, no TURN needed) ───
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ICE_SERVERS='[{"urls":["stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"]},{"urls":["stun:global.stun.twilio.com:3478"]}]'
#
# ─── Golden Path A: Tailscale VPN (dev cross-network) ───
# Replace <TAILSCALE_IP> with: tailscale ip -4
# Or just run: ./frontend/scripts/dev-clean-start-tailscale-https.sh
# (the script writes .env.local automatically)
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ICE_SERVERS='[{"urls":["stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"]},{"urls":["turn:<TAILSCALE_IP>:3478?transport=udp","turn:<TAILSCALE_IP>:3478?transport=tcp"],"username":"signchat","credential":"signchat"}]'
#
# ─── Golden Path B: Cloud VPS (production) ───
# Replace <PUBLIC_IP> and <TURN_PASS> with your VPS values.
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ICE_SERVERS='[{"urls":["stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"]},{"urls":["turn:<PUBLIC_IP>:3478?transport=udp","turn:<PUBLIC_IP>:3478?transport=tcp"],"username":"signchat","credential":"<TURN_PASS>"}]'
#
# ─── LAN-only (same Wi-Fi, no cross-network) ───
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ICE_SERVERS='[{"urls":["stun:stun.l.google.com:19302"]},{"urls":["turn:<LAN_IP>:3478?transport=udp","turn:<LAN_IP>:3478?transport=tcp"],"username":"signchat","credential":"signchat"}]'
